Projects

The Impact of Age and Excercise on Blood Melatonin Levels
Slide Deck  Finalized Report  - Created a Repeated Measures experiment and collected data three times across the span of three hours for over 100 people in “The Islands” program”  - Conducted ANOVA analysis, checked the validity of the data model, and did exploratory data analysis fo the results  - Later updated the experiment to include more data points and found new results to potentially conduct further research off of 


Stats 101C Regression Project
Final Report  - Worked with four other students to create the best possible predictive regression model for Amazon orders to predict the log total amount of an order - Created fifteen different models for my team for submission, including the team’s strongest model  - Collaborated on a final report and wrote about my specific model and the strengths and weaknesses of it 


Stats 101C Classification Project
Final Report  - Worked with three other students to create the best possible predictive model for 2020 election results for a county given the demographics and attributes of that county - Coded and submitted ten predictive models for our team  - Created five visuals for exploratory data analysis

title: About
text:
I’m currently a third year Statistics & Data Science Major and Accounting Minor at UCLA. For all my projects, I’m passionate about continuously working to find better ways to solve problems and to create the most optimal solution possible. My current focus for a career is in Tax Accounting, which I will be furthering via an internship this upcoming summer.
Outside of my academics and work, I love baking; playing video games, completing puzzles; taking Pilates and ballet classes; and spending time with my friends, family, and my two cats!
Fun Fact: my favorite theorem is the Infinite Monkey Theorem.
